\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf1\clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf1\clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf1\clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf1\clvertalt
\cellx2406
\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf1\clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf1\clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf1\clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf1\clvertalt
\cellx4548
\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf1\clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf1\clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf1\clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf1\clvertalt
\cellx6690
\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf1\clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf1\clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf1\clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf1\clvertalt
\cellx8370
\intbl\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb90\sa90\li45\ri45 Lumber Engineer Specialist Serf (LESS)
\intbl \cell
\intbl\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb90\sa90\li45\ri45 Can move to any neighbouring tile if it is currently in a field or peat bog tile.\par
\intbl\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb90\sa90\li45\ri45 This movement costs one fuel unless it is moving to or from a peat bog tile in which case it costs two fuel.\par
\intbl\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb90\sa90\li45\ri45 Cannot move if in a forest tile.
\intbl \cell
\intbl\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb90\sa90\li45\ri45 If given the \f2\fs20\sb0 saw\f1\fs22\sb90  command when in a forest tile will increase the player\u8217?s lumber supply by one.
\intbl \cell
\intbl\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb90\sa90\li45\ri45 Worth three victory points for opponent if destroyed.
\intbl \cell\pard\intbl\row\pard

\pard\trowd\ltrrow
\trgaph15\trleft570

\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf1\clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf1\clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf1\clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf1\clvertalt
\cellx2406
\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf1\clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf1\clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf1\clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf1\clvertalt
\cellx4548
\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf1\clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf1\clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf1\clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf1\clvertalt
\cellx6690
\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf1\clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf1\clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf1\clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf1\clvertalt
\cellx8370
\intbl\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb90\sa90\li45\ri45 Peat Bog Digger Serf (PBDS)
\intbl \cell
\intbl\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb90\sa90\li45\ri45 Can move to any neighbouring tile if it is currently in a field or forest tile. This movement costs two fuel.\par
\intbl\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb90\sa90\li45\ri45 Cannot move if in a peat bog tile.
\intbl \cell
\intbl\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb90\sa90\li45\ri45 If given the \f2\fs20\sb0 dig\f1\fs22\sb90  command when in a peat bog tile will increase the player\u8217?s fuel supply by either one or five.\par
\intbl\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb90\sa90\li45\ri45 The amount added depends on the result of a random number generation.
\intbl \cell
\intbl\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb90\sa90\li45\ri45 Worth two victory points for opponent if destroyed.
\intbl \cell\pard\intbl\row\pard
\pard
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 Player One\u8217?s pieces are displayed on the grid using uppercase letters (\f2\fs20\sb0 B\f1\fs22\sb240 , \f2\fs20\sb0 S\f1\fs22\sb240 , \f2\fs20\sb0 L\f1\fs22\sb240 , \f2\fs20\sb0 P\f1\fs22\sb240 ); Player Two\u8217?s pieces are displayed using lowercase letters (\f2\fs20\sb0 b\f1\fs22\sb240 , \f2\fs20\sb0 s\f1\fs22\sb240 , \f2\fs20\sb0 l\f1\fs22\sb240 , \f2\fs20\sb0 p\f1\fs22\sb240 ).\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 The \f2\fs20\sb0 upgrade\f1\fs22\sb240  command can be used to change one of the player\u8217?s serf pieces into a LESS or PBDS piece. When a piece is upgraded it costs five lumber.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 The \f2\fs20\sb0 spawn\f1\fs22\sb240  command can only be successfully used on an empty tile next to the player\u8217?s baron piece. An empty tile is one that does not contain a piece. It will add a new serf piece in the specified tile. When a piece is spawned it reduces the number of spare pieces available in the player\u8217?s supply by one and it costs three lumber.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 At the end of a turn the program checks to see if any pieces should be destroyed. A piece is destroyed if two (or more) of the tiles next to the tile the piece is in contain a piece.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 The table below shows some example commands that could be given at the start of the default game with descriptions of what they would do.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb0\sa0\li0\ri0 \~\par

